You&#39;re assuming that the position is for sure returning a value that you&#39;re casting to. When you do `SomeValue as SomeType` you are making the assertion that `SomeValue` is for sure an inheritor of `SomeType`.

If you don&#39;t know that that&#39;s the case, which in this case you don&#39;t since you have two possible types you can cast to. You have to check if a type `is` of a certain type before you cast it. 

If it&#39;s not, you&#39;ll get the error that you&#39;re getting `cannot cast x to y`

