I figured it out. I had to remove the `*ngIf` that wraps the table, which sucks because now I can&#39;t show a loading message, but it works!

    &lt;div class=&quot;example-container mat-elevation-z8&quot;&gt;
        &lt;mat-table #table [dataSource]=&quot;dataSource&quot; matSort&gt;
          &lt;ng-container *ngFor=&quot;let col of displayedColumns&quot; [matColumnDef]=&quot;col&quot;&gt;
            &lt;mat-header-cell *matHeaderCellDef mat-sort-header&gt; {{col}} &lt;/mat-header-cell&gt;
            &lt;mat-cell *matCellDef=&quot;let data&quot;&gt;
              &lt;!--  for mobile devices the columns collapse and each column is a row --&gt;
              &lt;span class=&quot;mobile-label&quot;&gt;{{col}}:&lt;/span&gt;
              {{data[col]}}
            &lt;/mat-cell&gt;
          &lt;/ng-container&gt;
          &lt;mat-header-row *matHeaderRowDef=&quot;displayedColumns&quot;&gt;&lt;/mat-header-row&gt;
          &lt;mat-row *matRowDef=&quot;let row; columns: displayedColumns;&quot;&gt;&lt;/mat-row&gt;
        &lt;/mat-table&gt;
        &lt;mat-paginator
          [pageSizeOptions]=&quot;pageSizeOptions&quot;
          showFirstLastButtons&gt;
        &lt;/mat-paginator&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

